# examples/ and validation/ hold tracked, CI-executed scripts. Only their
# *generated outputs* are ignored — via examples/.gitignore and
# validation/.gitignore — so a wholesale ignore here doesn't silently hide
# new scripts (or already-tracked reference figures) from git status
# (issue #374).
